{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17644783","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17644783"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:08:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:08:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18065"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18065","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18065"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.76,0.12,0.08,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10779"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74911"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10779","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10779"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18065"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60409"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5704"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25133"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25879"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74911","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74911"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EBrain death determination is a critical responsibility for medical practitioners that requires careful assessment and documentation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the minimum clinical criteria required for brain death certification?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Absence of spontaneous breathing with preserved pupillary reflexes","Complete loss of all brain stem functions confirmed by two doctors","Loss of cortical function with preserved brain stem reflexes","Persistent vegetative state for more than 24 hours","Unresponsive coma with preserved gag reflex"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003Ecomplete loss of all brain stem functions confirmed by two doctors\u003C/strong\u003E. Brain death requires the permanent and irreversible loss of all brain stem functions, which must be confirmed through rigorous clinical testing by two senior medical practitioners working independently.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELoss of cortical function with preserved brain stem reflexes\u003C/strong\u003E - Brain death requires loss of ALL brain stem functions, not just cortical functions\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbsence of spontaneous breathing with preserved pupillary reflexes\u003C/strong\u003E - The presence of any brain stem reflex (including pupillary response) excludes brain death\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUnresponsive coma with preserved gag reflex\u003C/strong\u003E - A preserved gag reflex indicates functioning brain stem and excludes brain death\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPersistent vegetative state for more than 24 hours\u003C/strong\u003E - Patients in a vegetative state retain brain stem functions and are not brain dead\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EClinical testing for brain death must demonstrate:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EComa with known cause\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EAbsence of brain stem reflexes (pupillary, corneal, vestibulo-ocular, gag, cough)\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EAbsence of spontaneous breathing (positive apnoea test)\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EExclusion of confounding factors (e.g. hypothermia, drugs)\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Brain death requires permanent loss of all brain stem functions including consciousness, breathing, and reflexes.","Clinical criteria for brain death include coma, absence of brain stem reflexes, and apnoea.","Two senior doctors must independently confirm brain death before certification."],"references":["Greer DM, Shemie SD, Lewis A, et al. Determination of Brain Death/Death by Neurologic Criteria The World Brain Death Project. JAMA. 2020; 324:1078-97.","Brain death. https://lexmedicus.com.au/brain-death/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60409"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18065"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60409","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60409"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-28T09:56:46+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-28T09:57:17+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10779"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74911"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synon